    "pop_culture": "As one of the nearest Sun-like stars, Tau Ceti has been the setting of numerous works of science fiction. Worlds around Tau Ceti provide the backdrop for “Project Hail Mary,” the 2026 movie and Andy Weir novel, and Ursula K. Le Guin’s anarchic utopia novel, \"The Dispossessed,\" whereas in Kim Stanley Robinson's novel, \"Aurora,\" travelers aim to colonize an Earth analog around Tau Ceti. Other authors who have featured Tau Ceti include Isaac Asimov, Arthur C. Clarke, Frank Herbert, and Robert Heinlein. A planet around Tau Ceti even serves as the setting for the 1968 film, \"Barbarella.”",
